values: Well you see theres this girl right...haha tragic line of my life.shes in my bio class. and shes gorgeous. she recently broke up with her boyfriend. the thing is i dont want to date her. i mean shes really nice and all but i just like talking to her. and her eyes are semi watery looking. where some people might hate that i think its gorgeous. i dont know my ideal of perfection anyway. back to real life.hmm i dont know. well my 19th birthday is saturday and the reason i bring this up is because of a discussion with stacia. how worthless is turning 19? what can you do? nothing...20 you can at least say hey im not a teen anymore.and 21 well...we all get it. anyway, it just seems worthless.speaking of which im currently writing a paper on the hypocrisy that is the republican party not because of bush but because of the 18th amendment...im sure ill post it on here when done at any rate it's four fifteen do you know where your pillow is? im going to find mine. laters

i just wanted to share these lyrics with the few who still read this it's a song called The Shame by The Blood Brothers a coheed/scremo mix and i really like this song and love the lyrics not much is new in life...enjoy the lyrics feel free to tell me what you think. i think theyre beautiful in a twisted way haha

My heart is a black haunted loom, weaving jackets for children who'll never be born.
My hands are abandoned factories manufacturing heartbreak and hate for the world.
As we waltz the broke dance of our limbs, this ballroom has been groped by so many evil whims.
As I drill the last hole into you, the wall of your body has hardened into glue.
Everything is going to be just awful when we're around.
All the color's gonna rot off your sight when we're around.
I remember the day that I sold my smile to that nice couple who lost their first child.
I threw in a set of sympathy, and a bucket of popcorn for the cemetery.
But now my face is all fenced off, the sky is boarded up, the hills covered in drop cloth.
How many chords till this song vomits out real love?
How many feathers to pluck naked the soiled dove?
How many whores till you send away for that trophy?
And how many punches till you give yourself away for free?
Because those bruises on your face look like the sun selling in disgrace.
(From these cliffs you can see the whole city laid out groveling like a field of wounded soldiers.
The billboards in heat and hissing, the sky scrappers stitching the gash of the earth.
As they waltz the broken dance of their limbs their ballroom has been groped by so many evil whims).
Everything is going to be just awful when we're around.
All the color's gonna rot off your sight when we're around.
I am just a salesman, pleased to meet you, can I show you around.
Everything must go, the shadows, the seagulls, when we're around.
This is our shame.

Laters

first off i want to say how much i love l-money (lindz) cause i dont know why she brightens my day with the simplist replys to my ranting and the fact that she read my whole post and shes cute to boot...what more could you want from a girl? shes looking i think guys...dont miss out on a great girl :-) anywho tonight was pretty eventful. i went to jens and gasp had a couple beers. nothing big and im not sure how i feel about it yet but im pretty sure ill be ok it was a few schmirnoffs cause i dont like beer but i just got warm nothing like some of the people there whos names i dont really know but they were rediculous.i felt bad for jen. after a while people left an it was me ray russ, patrick, and thomas rinker and some passed out guy. we rolled the passed out guy off the couch which was really funny and proceded to talk. for some reason ray was trying to hook up with some random girls. once he passed out we took his phone and started to call them back trying to get them to come over haha. it didnt work so me and project pat headed home. i got my case of abberations and ended up with 13 fiendish dire weasles and all but four of the minis...not too shabby. i am happy with that. tomorrow i think im going to go to some balloon thing with my rents since i will be gone for my bday its cool though cause i miss my little brothers a lot. hopefully i get to see their soccer teams. and apparently ron jeremey is going to be at vixens on my birthday...its ron jeremey...i dont like strip clubs but i would pay money to get my picture with a naked ron jeremey king of porn. i mean how many people have that? sadly well not sadly but ill be headed to richmond:-) im really feeling like a nerd. magic minis and posting two days in a row...man...laters

Well it has been quite a while since ive updated here but i figured i needed to do something other than watch bad hbo family movies at three in the morning about kids saving schools held hostage i mean one if your school was taken over would you really try and stop it? no. youd let it get blown to hell so you dont have to go.  anyway i have a lab practical in bio tomorrow so i should do well now that ive figure the easiest way to remember is hypo always flows to hyper and for those of you who dont know what i am talking about you sure are lucky.  the new abberations set for a minis game i play is released today so i get my 2 cases in a little over 12 hours... you can tell im excited.  it was my birthday present from my dad.  school is going well. it's rather easy but then again it's thirteenth grade. i spend most of my days with michael at the game haven now so i nerd out a lot.were going down to states on my birthday the 23rd wink wink for magic down in richmond. a great present for me a nice two and a half hour drive down and possibly back up depending on whether or not were staying at jasons sisters.well i havent see much of anyone else lately. i miss arin and mary alot :-( but i should be meeting up with each of them sometime soon id suppose.  Im not sure about much else right now.  i should be getting a new job at dominos as a driver soon.  im not sure how i feel about that. it's cash in pocket but its a dominos driver. money is money though i suppose. i actually like school now. psychology is amazing. aside from stephanie and my jokes about everyone in our head being a drug addict, it intrests me greatly.  that and of course history. everything else is pretty lame i tested out of english and i think im dropping econ because i dont have the effort or motivation right now it takes to get an A in the class. i got a B on my first test but... i have never been one to try hard haha. i also hung out with lia the other day. even though it was only 15 minutes it was refreshing. i miss talking to her and just being somewhat goofy but having her to talk to about serious things is nice too. even though she didnt give me much advice i feel with her i have some weird understanding like just talking to her alliviates my issues. its nice because shes one of the few people i feel like that about. im also thinking about taking the summer off instead of attending school to get done sooner to go work at church camp again. i love it down there and i feel like i need something to get God more involved in my life because i seem to be losing things there a little. and now as im sure you all know my take on politics and the debates. im not sure how i feel about kerry at this point. i just know im not voting for bush. aside from the jokes about kerry looking like tree beard from lord of the rings, i will probably vote for him.im not sure how much longer i can tolerate american politics. i just realized the other day why it bothers me. religion has no place in politics.the seperation of church and state goes both ways and americans are the only ones who dont realize that. i am against abortion because of my religion. but i realize socially to make it illegal would be silly. you would have unhealthy abortions in alleys etc i would not want my wife/friend/whomever to have an abortion but it is their choice. personally im not going to have the problem because im not knocking anyone up unless im ready to have the child. i think maybe im coping out but i have my belief but realize the importance of the choice for sake of everyones safety. but i also dont say liberals who do it are going to hell. george bush is running on the idea of Jesus being his homeboy...need i say more? i believe in Jesus but i am detested by school prayer and what bush is trying to do. it's bad enough the only catholic president we had was killed early on. well enough ranting on worthless subjects iron chef is on so i must away...laters

i just need a change...someplace i can go where no one knows me and i dont know anyone else and the only interaction i have with other people is what is highly needed.  i dont need "friends" the only ones id need are two i barely get to talk to now and thats enough for me. all of these "friends" just bring my down when i just get into stupid arguements or quarrells with them about things that dont even matter and yet they get really upset at me or they have found someone new to be with (and no thats not lia and brendan that falls under maaaannnnyyy people just so we all know that) or they feel now that they have more friends they dont need many anymore. i think blood for blood said it best "the world we live in is going straight to hell.  the fellas i know have nowhere to turn, were all living in exile." i guess my main problem is people i know. you all are so inconsiderate as to the needs of others. all you care about is me me me me me and yeah we all get like that but not all the time. people are more important than any of you out there so you might want to start caring about them more than you care about yourself. dont look at whats good for self look at whats good for most. im sure Gandhi wasnt happy when he was fasting...but look at something...we consider him one of the greatest social heros of all time. i wont bring Jesus up because thats an easy arguement. mother theresa gave her life and lived a middle class life but helped others...maybe you all could take a lesson and you say well fatty what have you done? *cue venting time so those of you who dont want to read this can go back to your email* well ive helped a girl get through some of the hardest times in her life and got abused through it but stuck with it and now shes one of the happiest people i know WITHOUT ME...i have been there for many people for many experiences they shouldnt have had to go through stood by friends who just want me around when they need me and people who only come around when its tough on them and need someone they can USE for a little while. ive grown up in a house where talking to my little brothers can cause problems between me and my parents. yet i dont bitch a lot in person i may do it a hell of a lot on here or online but i dont say how hard my life is or how bad i have it.im obviously typing this from a computer so it cant be all that bad eh? far many people have it worse than me and im sick of NEARLY EVERYONE thinking its not their job to help them. why dont you go back to nursing on your mom and being protected little conservative drones. and another thing...if you are American...dont talk about politics. American politics are like a joke with no punchline. everyone laughs but no one really gets it. i guess youre better than people who say politics dont concern them...and to your democrats/republicans...aka stupid idiots in the middle that want to pretend theyre conservative and liberal there are no politics to starving...wake up and fucking do something with your life and mine other than argue about which president smoked the most dope in high school or which one dodged the war...and you wonder why people want to kill everyone in our nation? its because they all think were like you...we need a new for of society that isnt MILDLY RETARDED. you know the difference between Castro, Moa Ze Dong, Hiltler and you all? they were acttualy trying to help someone other than themseleves with their "brutal tyranny." now whos the brutal ones? the one helping a nation or the ones helping themselves? grow up

well lately ive been in a good mood but right now im feeling rather somber for some reason....so im not sure what all thats about. well i think i know why. here lately ive hung out and talked with mary quite a bit which has been....amazing to say the least. i dont know why its just...so refreshing ever time im with her...its like i could never get tired of her. i met her at church camp two summers ago when i consuled and she was a camper and we met up again at another show recently. i mean today for instance i went over to her house today and had a blast doing nothing haha i mean she was washing dishes and she got me wet so you can imagine where this went...yes a water fight and bubble fight to follow and its the little things that i dont know...i dont think i could have as much fun or be like that with other people. and i feel like shes one of my oldest friends...im just worried about rushing into something or hurting her especially with how she has conveyed her past to me. i dont think i would ever hurt her as much as she has been but i dont want to at all...shes a sophmore at strasburg...almost 17 for those of you out there always commenting on my girl age...(ARIN) haha i threw that in just for you...which reminds me...i dont know i think for some reason Arins mood lately has acctually lifted mine. i think because maybe we used to be in the same problem and now since she found Brent and is stoked i figure i can be to. so i guess thank you arin : ) anyway...well talking about this has acctually improved my mood ten fold. i dont know...some people may find her different...but i like her. and she makes me happy for the first time in a long time. thanks to all of you who put up with my shit and crappy moods...hopefully all of that will be gone for good...oh well if its not...i can stay stuck in this moment : ) laters

Ever had one of those days that was just going amazingly well for no reason at all? fell asleep in all your classes but didnt miss anything? went to work and had a great day there? then have something totally ruin it? i hate these nights...well i wont get into it all but let me talk about why today was a good day because i should be more optomistic...right anyways...i got up early got ready for school...was at chelseas early she came out early so inevitably...we got to school early. i went and talked to some people and such wasnt rushed to class it was going good.  went to sleep in precal apparently i snored during the test...sorry Arin haha went to Government and semi enjoyed that amazingly enough thats how you know its a good day...when chris doesnt hate government. then off to Frantz where we talked about stuff... gimme a sec to remember what...oh cinema and that was awesome...then cain sucked so i slept lunch was classic...bio was pretty good genetics are easy...and history another sleeper. went to the young dems meeting after school...which was odd because i find myself questioning my stand...i have found much appeal in anarchism as far as...government..just sucks...communism is a great theory but no matter what someone will f up government somewhere so im hearby on hiatus...i guess im thinking between socialism and anarchism...and i know you rolling your eyes not the lame anarchism that the kids represent on their shirts...but the real kind the social harmony and moral ethics gasps...i know we normally call people who think like that hippies...anyway after that i went to ems to get my christmas present a homecoming picture of us framed :) so awesome...i love it..anyways then i went to work me and marcus made fun of lindsey most of the night and then i went to the swim meet which was really cool. got to talk to some people i dont normally get to see much anymore and now im babbling on here...what else is new...ima try to update this more frequently now but alas its almost midnight im off to bed laters

except for a little confrontation at the end of the night between you guessed it me and Em all was well i really liked brent and i though him and arin were cute together : / im not getting into that one but im happy shes happy :D work is ok school is about to start and thats good because it will cut back my hours i got emily a sweet ass camera which i probably spent too much on but shell enjoy it and thats worth more that i could ever have. i have to switch out of rosenthals class because she hates me haha oh well what can you do? i guess now its time to close out the year with a cliche event... my resolutions..

"The silence that lingers between swung fists and slit wrists is enough to make me kill myself  Enough for me to will myself and fill myself with what I'll never have.  You are long gone and that makes my life all wrong theres no music to my song just the sound of bleeding on and on. On this day you wont hear a word nor a tear will drop from fear for the end is now here.  see i just take this knife and i give it a slice and that will end all my strife along will my life and see thats not so bad cause who'll get sad? a few may get mad but this tainted dove can not go above so do not hold a grudge cause you were the last that i ever loved..."

you know who i miss? my college friends...i hope someone misses me as much as i miss emily and stacia.  i really miss them when i listen to Our lady Peace for some reason. well i really dont have much to say...life is as it has been girlfriendless and worthless feeling.  mainly all i wanted to say is that i can only imagine what losing them for good will be like because it sucks now...i might die when they do...i miss them and i will miss everyone i see now.  sometimes growing up isnt maturing...its giving up all the goofy friends and goofy times you and your friends have...i will miss nights on trampolines the three hour drives to charlottesville eloping to gore the endless daycare shows and the anticipation in the week before them final goodbyes in the center cinema parking lots and i will mostly miss the $2.09 roses from walmart four or five times a month talking on my cell phone staring through windows at the person on the other end with them staring back. if growing up means i cant have these memories that have made me happiest again...someone kill me now because i dont want to grow another day older. i love you all i think you know who you are by those references. laters.
